WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.300 --> 00:00:08.500
Teams are already using AI to summarise claims, cases, support tickets, and internal documents.

2
00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:15.500
But sensitive data often sits inside the prompt before anyone notices.

3
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:23.500
NeutralAI adds a control layer before that prompt reaches an external model.

4
00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:31.500
Paste a real workflow prompt, then run masking.

5
00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:43.000
Names, emails, phone numbers, IBANs, card numbers, and other sensitive spans are detected and replaced with safe tokens.

6
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:51.500
The original prompt stays available for review, while the sanitized version is what moves forward.

7
00:00:51.500 --> 00:01:00.000
Security and legal teams can see what was found, how it was classified, and why it was masked.

8
00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:08.800
For workflows that need controlled restoration, reversible tokens can preserve business context without exposing raw identifiers by default.

9
00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:15.360
NeutralAI helps regulated teams use AI with clearer boundaries, cleaner evidence, and less sensitive data leaving the business. Try the playground, or book a live walkthrough to map this to your own AI workflow.
